<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-04-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-04-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="957" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d957">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 23905/3A.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Taft</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">President of Venezuela</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">The
                                        White House</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-19"><hi rend="italic">April 19,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>On this centennial anniversary of the independence of the Republic of
                            Venezuela I have the honor to convey to your excellency and to <pb facs="0979" n="867" xml:id="pg_867"/> the Government and people of
                            Venezuela the congratulations and good wishes of the Government and
                            people of the United States of America and my own personal best wishes
                            for the continued success of your administration.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. H. Taft.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>